&lt;p&gt;An exciting and opportunity has arisen for a dynamic and enthusiastic senior nurse, passionate about education to join the Emergency Nursing Team at Northwick Park Hospital in the role of Practice Development Nurse.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Practice Educator Role is essential influencing learning and the professional development of the nursing staff by providing support and educational input. Seeing approximately 104,000 patients per year we are seeking a visionary motivated individual to inspire and drive best practice in partnership with another practice development nurse and Educational Lead Nurse among our 186 nurses within the unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for an individual who has significant clinical experience within emergency care and education. Previous experience as an emergency practice educator is desirable. The role is a great opportunity for emergency nurse who is interested in the quality and development of the emergency nursing role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The aim is to ensure the ED delivers a high standard of care so we will be looking for the right candidate to help the educational team to take it one step further and enhance our educational program such as the Emergency foundation and Capital Led Qualification in Specialism Emergency Course and deliver the Trauma Level 1 program in line with the national competency standard recommended by the National Major Trauma Nursing Group (NMTNG).&lt;/p&gt;
